This SQL-based data analysis project explores transactional data from a pizza restaurant to uncover sales trends, customer preferences, and business performance insights. The dataset includes detailed information about orders, pizza types, prices, quantities, and timestamps.

ðŸ“Š Key Analyses Performed:
Total Revenue Calculation: Derived overall sales by joining order details with pizza pricing.

Daily Sales Performance: Analyzed daily revenue and identified dates with sales higher than the average.

Cumulative Revenue Trend: Used window functions to track how revenue accumulated over time.

Category-wise Revenue Share: Computed the percentage contribution of each pizza category to total revenue.

Sales by Pizza Size & Category: Identified most popular pizza sizes and categories by both order count and quantity.

Hourly Demand Insights: Extracted peak ordering hours to support staffing and marketing decisions.

Top 3 Pizza Types per Category (by Revenue): Used ROW_NUMBER() window function to determine bestsellers in each category.

ðŸ§° Tools & Skills Used:
SQL (MySQL): Joins, subqueries, window functions, aggregations, filtering, and groupings.

Data Cleaning: Ensured consistency in table relationships and keys.

Analytical Thinking: Framed business questions and translated them into efficient SQL queries.

